Document: ArrayOccluder3D  
Path: godot/classes/class_arrayoccluder3d.rst  
Summary: Properties for defining the occluder's indices and vertex positions in 3D space.  

PackedInt32Array **indices** = PackedInt32Array()  
Method: set_indices(value: PackedInt32Array) → void  
Method: get_indices() → PackedInt32Array  
The occluder's index position. Indices determine which points from the vertices array should be drawn and in which order. Note: The occluder is always updated after setting this value. If creating occluders procedurally, consider using set_arrays() instead to avoid updating the occluder twice when it's created. Note: The returned array is copied and any changes to it will not update the original property value.  

PackedVector3Array **vertices** = PackedVector3Array()  
Method: set_vertices(value: PackedVector3Array) → void  
Method: get_vertices() → PackedVector3Array  
The occluder's vertex positions in local 3D coordinates. Note: The occluder is always updated after setting this value. If creating occluders procedurally, consider using set_arrays() instead to avoid updating the occluder twice when it's created. Note: The returned array is copied and any changes to it will not update the original property value.
---CHUNK---
Document: ArrayOccluder3D
Path: godot/classes/class_arrayoccluder3d.rst
Summary: Method to set vertices and indices arrays for an occluder, updating the occluder once after both are assigned.

Method: set_arrays(vertices: PackedVector3Array, indices: PackedInt32Array) → void
Sets vertices and indices properties, updating the occluder geometry only after both arrays are assigned. The method ensures the occluder is rebuilt once when both parameters are set, rather than on each individual assignment.